HEADWORD: Consonantize
<hw>Con"so*nant*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To change
into, or use as, a consonant.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The vowel is
<xex>consonantized</xex>, that is, made closer in position.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Peile.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

